This Resource may be created on the OCF Server that is capable of
rendering speech by an OCF Client and allows the client to provide an
SSML document with text to render or may be created on the OIC Server
by some resident application. The audio rendered is at this stage
local to the Server (i. e. not streamed). The utterance is an SSML
document. The supportedLanguages is an array of the RFC5646 defined
language tags that are supported. The supportedVoices is an SSML
document fragment indicating the voices that are supported. Utterance
in the example shall be a properly escaped (JSON rules) SSML
title of the movie is: "Monty Pythons The Meaning of Life" which is
The array of supported language tags.
The SSML document fragment indicating supported voices.
The SSML document including the speech body.
